All eyes are on China, as the world waits for the opening ceremony on Friday night. Expectations are high that a successful Winter Olympics may just be what the doctors ordered to return the world to normalcy from the pandemic. The Olympics remind us that while we may come from different countries and regions and speak different languages, we are all together for a shared future. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Zheng Junfeng says three buzzwords define the opening ceremony.